      "agentResultText": "Done. Here's a summary of all changes:\n\n### Database\n- Added `archived_at` nullable column to the `tasks` table (via migration script + updated seed script)\n- Updated `TaskTable` in `src/lib/db.ts` with `archived_at: string | null`\n- Updated `Task` interface in `src/lib/mock-data.ts` with `archivedAt: string | null` (also removed dead mock data arrays, keeping only type definitions)\n\n### Query layer (`src/lib/queries.ts`)\n- `mapTask()` now maps `archived_at` to `archivedAt`\n- `getTasksForProject()`, `getTaskCountForProject()`, `getAllTasks()`, `getDashboardStats()`, `getProjectsWithTaskCounts()`, `getFilteredTasksForProject()` — all now filter with `WHERE archived_at IS NULL` so archived tasks are excluded from normal listings\n- `createTask()` — explicitly sets `archived_at: null`\n- **New**: `archiveTask(taskId, projectId)` — sets `archived_at` to current timestamp\n- **New**: `restoreTask(taskId, projectId)` — sets `archived_at` back to `null`\n- **New**: `getArchivedTasksForProject(projectId)` — returns only tasks where `archived_at IS NOT NULL`\n\n### API endpoints\n- `POST /api/projects/[id]/tasks/[taskId]/archive` — calls `archiveTask()`, returns the updated task\n- `POST /api/projects/[id]/tasks/[taskId]/restore` — calls `restoreTask()`, returns the updated task\n\n### UI\n- **`src/app/projects/[id]/archive-task-button.tsx`** — Client component with `ArchiveTaskButton` and `RestoreTaskButton` that POST to the respective endpoints and call `router.refresh()`\n- **Project detail page** — \"Move\" column renamed to \"Actions\", each row now has both the Move dropdown and an Archive button\n- **Archived page** (`/projects/[id]/archived`) — Now queries and displays archived tasks in a full table with Status, Priority, Assignee, Due Date columns and a Restore button per row",
